## Graph Chat: forward X-Forwarded-* headers on loopback (deployed 302 fix)

Bug: in the deployed Databricks App, Graph Chat reported
"HTTP 302 — the server returned a redirect" when calling the internal
`/dtwin/graphql/schema` / `/dtwin/graphql/execute` / `/dtwin/execute`
routes. Root cause: the agent's loopback HTTPX client forwarded the
user's session cookies but not the Databricks-injected
`X-Forwarded-*` identity headers, so `PermissionMiddleware` resolved
the internal call as anonymous and 302-redirected it to
`/access-denied?reason=app`. Locally, `is_databricks_app()` returns
False and the middleware short-circuits to admin, masking the issue.

Fix: capture the incoming request's `X-Forwarded-*` / `X-Real-*` /
`X-CSRF-Token` / `Referer` headers in `dtwin_assistant_chat` and
thread them through `run_chat_agent(..., session_headers=...)` →
`ToolContext.dtwin_session_headers` → the loopback `httpx.Client`.
Also disabled redirect-following so a future 3xx is raised as a clear
error rather than silently resolved.

