## Graph Chat: all tools now use session-aware internal routes

Bug (follow-up): after fixing the 302 redirect, Graph Chat still
returned `"no versions found for domain <name>"` when asking for the
status / stats / entity search, because `tool_get_status`,
`tool_list_entity_types` and `tool_describe_entity` still hit the
public `/api/v1/digitaltwin/{status,stats,triples/find}` routes which
resolve the domain through the registry and require a published
version.

Fix: re-pointed the three remaining tools at the session-aware
internal equivalents so Graph Chat works against any in-session
domain, published or not:

- `tool_list_entity_types` → `GET /dtwin/sync/stats`
- `tool_get_status`        → `GET /dtwin/sync/status`
- `tool_describe_entity`   → `GET /dtwin/triples/find` (new route,
  mirrors the public one but resolves the domain from the user
  session instead of the registry).

