2026-04-22 -- Digital Twin: actionable VIEW error diagnostics

Problem:
A deployed-app user reported a sync failure surfacing the generic message
"The database reported an error that does not match a known column-resolution
pattern. Verify your source tables and column mappings." The real underlying
Databricks error was PERMISSION_DENIED (service principal missing MANAGE on a
stale TABLE occupying the target VIEW name from a prior materialized-mode
build), but diagnose_view_error() only recognized UNRESOLVED_COLUMN shapes and
swallowed everything else into a generic fallback.

Fix:
- DigitalTwin.diagnose_view_error() now recognizes two additional error
  families produced by the Databricks SQL engine and returns actionable text:
    * PERMISSION_DENIED -> explains MANAGE/SELECT grants needed by the app SP
      and calls out the "stale TABLE blocking CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW" case.
    * TABLE_OR_VIEW_NOT_FOUND -> names the missing 3-part identifier and
      advises verifying catalog/schema/table + SELECT grants.
- For any unrecognized shape, the fallback now includes a truncated (<=500
  chars) raw DB message so admins can act without having to dig in server
  logs first. The full message is still logged at WARNING via logger.warning.

Tests (additive):
- tests/test_dtwin_service.py:TestDiagnoseViewError (5 new cases)
    * permission_denied_is_recognised
    * table_or_view_not_found_is_recognised
    * unresolved_column_with_mapping_context (regression guard)
    * unknown_error_includes_raw_detail
    * unknown_error_truncates_very_long_detail

