2026-04-22 -- Deployment guide: Unity Catalog grants for the app SP

Motivation:
The previous deployment guide covered warehouse/volume resource bindings and
the in-app RBAC model, but said nothing about the Unity Catalog privileges the
app's service principal needs on the registry catalog/schema, the registry
volume, and the source tables referenced by R2RML mappings. Missing UC grants
are the most common cause of Digital Twin sync failures (surfaced today as
PERMISSION_DENIED or TABLE_OR_VIEW_NOT_FOUND from CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW).

Added (docs/deployment.md):
- New top-level section "3. Unity Catalog Permissions for the Service
  Principal" (sub-sections 3.1-3.7):
    3.1 Operation matrix mapping every UC-touching runtime action to the
        UC privilege it needs (SHOW/DESCRIBE, SELECT on sources, CREATE
        OR REPLACE VIEW, incremental snapshot CREATE TABLE + DROP, fallback
        DATABRICKS_TRIPLESTORE_TABLE CREATE/DELETE/INSERT, Volume I/O,
        and the optional REST create-volume call).
    3.2 Copy-paste SQL for registry catalog/schema grants (minimum viable
        set + short ALL PRIVILEGES variant for dev).
    3.3 Copy-paste SQL for source-table grants (per-table and schema-wide
        patterns).
    3.4 Explicit list of grants the app does NOT need (MODIFY on sources,
        MANAGE on registry schema/catalog).
    3.5 "Stale TABLE blocking CREATE OR REPLACE VIEW" pitfall with the
        exact DROP TABLE remediation (the real cause of the user-reported
        sync failure).
    3.6 SP ID discovery guidance (client-id vs app-alias email).
    3.7 Verification queries (SHOW GRANTS / SHOW TABLES / SHOW VOLUMES).
- Prerequisites table in section 2 now cross-links to section 3.
- Troubleshooting section (now 11): two new entries, one for the
  PERMISSION_DENIED "Failed to create VIEW" flow and one for
  TABLE_OR_VIEW_NOT_FOUND, each linking back to the relevant 3.x section.
  Existing "Connection Errors" bullet now links to section 3.
- Full Deployment Checklist (now 10): added step 10 for UC grants.
- New Workspace Checklist (in 5): added a UC-grants step.

Renumbering:
- Sections 3-11 renumbered to 4-12 with zero cross-reference impact (the
  file contains no "see section N" links). The TOC-like Overview table
  continues to work unchanged because it doesn't reference section numbers.

Other docs:
- docs/README.md: the "Deployment" row in the doc map now mentions UC
  grants explicitly.

